Module io.winterframework.mod.configuration
Package io.winterframework.mod.configuration

Interface ExecutableConfigurationUpdate<A extends ConfigurationUpdate<A,​B,​C>,​B extends ExecutableConfigurationUpdate<A,​B,​C>,​C extends ConfigurationUpdateResult<?>>

Type Parameters:
A - the update type
B - the executable update type
C - the update result type
All Known Implementing Classes:
RedisConfigurationSource.RedisExecutableConfigurationUpdate
public interface ExecutableConfigurationUpdate<A extends ConfigurationUpdate<A,​B,​C>,​B extends ExecutableConfigurationUpdate<A,​B,​C>,​C extends ConfigurationUpdateResult<?>>

An executable configuration update can be executed to set configuration properties for a particular context in a configuration source.

Multiple configuration updates can be chained by calling the and() method to be executed in a batch when the execute() method is invoked on the last query.

Since:
1.0
Author:
Jeremy Kuhn
See Also:
ConfigurationUpdate, ConfigurationUpdateResult
